title: bcm43430: thanks to mame82, we can now add an additional mon0 interface on the…
message:
bcm43430: thanks to mame82, we can now add an additional mon0 interface on the raspberry pi 3 to send monitor mode frames only to this interface, while sending regular Ethernet frames to wlan0. That allows to connect to an access point and at the same time run monitor mode. The feature does not run smoothly yet, bit it is fine for alpha testing.
Run the following commands to test it:
nexutil -m6
ifconfig mon0 up
tcpdump -i mon0

title: nexutil, libnexio: nexutil can now communicate with the firmware without root…
message: nexutil, libnexio: nexutil can now communicate with the firmware without root priviledges over udp using the -X switch. However, you need a valid security cookie and the wlan interface needs the ip 192.168.222.1 with netmask 255.255.255.0. If it has a different ip, you can set the target broadcast address with the -B switch.

message: bcm4339: added the ability to inject frames or to inject ioctls that are tunneled over udp.

title: common: added a udp tunneling function to send udp frames from the firmware to…
message: common: added a udp tunneling function to send udp frames from the firmware to Android. This will be used for tunneling monitor mode frames and to send answers to ioctl requests back to the calling application.

title: common: added code to set, get and check a security cookie. It is intended to be…
message: common: added code to set, get and check a security cookie. It is intended to be set by an ioctl using nexutil, for example. As sending ioctls requires root priviledges, those users who can set the cookie, can be assumed to have root priviledges. In a next step the cookie will be used to authenticate the communication with the firmware using udp frames that can either contain frames for injection or ioctls. Using this approch, an app without root priviledges can use monitor mode and frame injection as long as it knows the set security cookie.
